external_knowledge:
- "hardware setups" refers to distinct hardware configurations;
- "average day-long CPU usage" corresponds to the average CPU utilization over the course of the day for each hardware configuration;
- "sorted from the most to least busy ones" means the results are ordered by decreasing average CPU utilization.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT pc.config_id
FROM performance_metrics pc
WHERE pc.bw_mb_s > (SELECT AVG(bw_mb_s) FROM performance_metrics);

SELECT AVG(power_consumption) AS average_power_consumption
FROM performance_metrics
WHERE config_id = 0 AND disk_utilization > 70;

SELECT hc.name, dc.contact_email
FROM hardware_configurations AS hc
INNER JOIN data_centers AS dc ON hc.data_center_id = dc.data_center_id;

external_knowledge:
Larger data centers: total capacity > 1000;
Recent past year: installed in 2022;
Really fast average speed: average clock speed > 3.0 GHz;

- "Latest performance details" refer to the most recent performance metrics;
- "Network speed" corresponds to the bandwidth (bw_mb_s) and network latency (network_latency);
- "CPU usage" refers to the CPU utilization percentage (cpu_utilization);
- "Most recent user access information" pertains to the latest access log entry for a given metric, including user's full name (user_name) and IP address (ip_address).

- 'Struggling with high resource usage' refers to configurations where CPU, memory, or disk utilization exceeds 90%.;
- 'Overcrowded data centers' means those with a total capacity of over 1000 units and a current capacity that exceeds 80% of the total capacity.;
- 'Detailed hardware setups' includes the configuration ID, name, description, and performance metrics (CPU, memory, disk utilizations) along with data center specifics like location and manager contact details.;
- Results are prioritized by the highest overall resource usage first.
